329
00:34:23,896 --> 00:34:26,956
MAI'S VOICE

330
00:34:28,901 --> 00:34:32,894
The incident happened to Mr. Fujita.

331
00:34:33,272 --> 00:34:37,142
After his only daughter Mai died and

332
00:34:37,142 --> 00:34:40,339
He had just finished his 7th day of mourning.

333
00:34:45,117 --> 00:34:46,880
Mai.

334
00:34:47,219 --> 00:34:50,211
You'll get dizzy.

335
00:34:50,856 --> 00:34:52,619
Mai!

336
00:34:54,860 --> 00:35:03,202
It was the voice of his dead daughter.

337
00:35:03,202 --> 00:35:04,736
I just heard things...

338
00:35:04,736 --> 00:35:06,572
It was great

339
00:35:06,572 --> 00:35:09,408
for Fujita to hear her voice.

340
00:35:09,408 --> 00:35:11,842
Even it was only in his imagination.

341
00:35:12,411 --> 00:35:14,847
It's not your imagination.

342
00:35:14,847 --> 00:35:17,975
Mai!

343
00:35:21,053 --> 00:35:23,544
Mai's Voice

344
00:35:26,892 --> 00:35:31,263
Their daughter's death filled them with grief.

345
00:35:31,263 --> 00:35:34,130
It tore the couples heart in 2.

346
00:35:35,367 --> 00:35:38,495
It was painful.

347
00:35:38,670 --> 00:35:40,639
Then one day...

348
00:35:40,639 --> 00:35:42,708
Keep your chin up, Daddy.

349
00:35:42,708 --> 00:35:44,309
Mai.

350
00:35:44,309 --> 00:35:47,446
I'll be fine.

351
00:35:47,446 --> 00:35:48,881
I'll do my best.

352
00:35:48,881 --> 00:35:52,417
He discovered that he alone

353
00:35:52,417 --> 00:35:55,187
could communicate with her.

354
00:35:55,187 --> 00:35:56,822
Mr. Fujita?

355
00:35:56,822 --> 00:35:58,757
Here is...

356
00:35:58,757 --> 00:36:01,658
His mind was always elsewhere.

357
00:36:02,661 --> 00:36:06,791
His wife worked at a bar.

358
00:36:07,032 --> 00:36:12,629
But her customers couldn't console her.

359
00:36:14,806 --> 00:36:17,673
You're over-filling.

360
00:36:19,278 --> 00:36:24,341
She, too, began to hear Mai's voice.

361
00:36:25,384 --> 00:36:27,352
One day,

362
00:36:27,352 --> 00:36:30,889
Mr. Fujita visited his wife's bar.

363
00:36:30,889 --> 00:36:34,393
You don't normally come here.

364
00:36:34,393 --> 00:36:37,462
What are you wearing?

365
00:36:37,462 --> 00:36:42,331
We're having a fancy dress party tonight.

366
00:36:42,734 --> 00:36:48,104
It was organized by a regular customer.

367
00:36:48,907 --> 00:36:53,412
We're doing this to cheer your wife up.

368
00:36:53,412 --> 00:36:56,609
His colleague was there, too.

369
00:36:56,982 --> 00:37:00,085
But it hardly raised his spirits.

370
00:37:00,085 --> 00:37:03,522
He couldn't share their enthusiasm.

371
00:37:03,522 --> 00:37:09,324
Mai, I'm on my own.

372
00:37:10,562 --> 00:37:13,198
I can't forgive them.

373
00:37:13,198 --> 00:37:15,200
Mai!

374
00:37:15,200 --> 00:37:17,035
He couldn't see her.

375
00:37:17,035 --> 00:37:21,106
But he could feel her presence.

376
00:37:21,106 --> 00:37:26,066
He couldn't take anymore and left the bar.

377
00:37:28,981 --> 00:37:31,108
Mr. Fujita!

378
00:37:31,249 --> 00:37:33,080
Mr. Fujita!

379
00:37:34,286 --> 00:37:35,721
Reiko...

380
00:37:35,721 --> 00:37:38,256
I thought that was you.

381
00:37:38,256 --> 00:37:39,424
He bumped

382
00:37:39,424 --> 00:37:45,056
into Reiko, an old flame.

383
00:37:47,699 --> 00:37:51,837
Out of regret or loneliness...

384
00:37:51,837 --> 00:37:57,036
He drunk enough to forget his pain.

385
00:38:05,817 --> 00:38:10,489
When he awoke he found himself in the hotel.

386
00:38:10,489 --> 00:38:12,480
Oh, no!

387
00:38:14,860 --> 00:38:17,396
Hello...

388
00:38:17,396 --> 00:38:21,423
Could you wait a little?

389
00:38:22,634 --> 00:38:25,228
Oh, no.

390
00:38:26,605 --> 00:38:28,129
Mai?

391
00:38:30,342 --> 00:38:33,834
What am I doing here?

392
00:38:34,546 --> 00:38:37,879
Sorry to keep you waiting. Mr. Fujita?

393
00:38:38,650 --> 00:38:42,586
His conscience forced him to return home.

394
00:38:44,089 --> 00:38:46,216
I'm home.

395
00:38:49,461 --> 00:38:51,063
Hello.

396
00:38:51,063 --> 00:38:53,732
After my customers left the bar,

397
00:38:53,732 --> 00:38:55,834
they were in a car accident.

398
00:38:55,834 --> 00:38:59,037
3 of them!

399
00:38:59,037 --> 00:39:00,238
What!

400
00:39:00,238 --> 00:39:02,207
I heard...

401
00:39:02,207 --> 00:39:05,911
Mai saying I can't forgive them.

402
00:39:05,911 --> 00:39:08,980
Then, Fujita heard her...

403
00:39:08,980 --> 00:39:12,284
You are dirty, Daddy.

404
00:39:12,284 --> 00:39:15,447
That was the last they heard from Mai.

405
00:39:15,487 --> 00:39:18,012
The End

406
00:39:18,557 --> 00:39:21,458
THE PROMISE

407
00:39:24,830 --> 00:39:27,233
Mine went further.

408
00:39:27,233 --> 00:39:30,336
We were inseparable.

409
00:39:30,336 --> 00:39:32,972
I was so happy to see her

410
00:39:32,972 --> 00:39:35,270
that I enjoyed going visiting her.

411
00:39:37,877 --> 00:39:38,811
Granny!

412
00:39:38,811 --> 00:39:39,945
What Osamu?

413
00:39:39,945 --> 00:39:42,281
Are you going to die one day?

414
00:39:42,281 --> 00:39:45,051
Of course.

415
00:39:45,051 --> 00:39:47,119
I've never seen a ghost.

416
00:39:47,119 --> 00:39:50,256
Can you return as a ghost for me?

417
00:39:50,256 --> 00:39:52,958
For you, I will.

418
00:39:52,958 --> 00:39:55,628
I will come and see you

419
00:39:55,628 --> 00:39:56,829
Really?

420
00:39:56,829 --> 00:40:02,902
But you must promise me
not get frightened.

421
00:40:02,902 --> 00:40:05,700
I won't.

422
00:40:06,906 --> 00:40:09,275
You're my Granny.

423
00:40:09,275 --> 00:40:11,877
Promise?

424
00:40:11,877 --> 00:40:14,380
Yes.

425
00:40:14,380 --> 00:40:16,349
I will return, you know.

426
00:40:16,349 --> 00:40:18,146
I won't get frightened.

427
00:40:19,819 --> 00:40:22,379
She died sometime ago.

428
00:40:22,588 --> 00:40:26,025
I was sad but my only consolation

429
00:40:26,025 --> 00:40:28,118
was she died without suffering.

430
00:41:09,902 --> 00:41:13,429
Were you frightened?

431
00:41:15,741 --> 00:41:18,767
I was dead scared.

432
00:41:27,353 --> 00:41:29,878
Don't be frightened.

433
00:41:32,425 --> 00:41:33,559
I was scared.

434
00:41:33,559 --> 00:41:35,694
Shit! I was frightened.

435
00:41:35,694 --> 00:41:37,719
Damn!

436
00:41:38,597 --> 00:41:42,897
It was the 7th day of mourning.

437
00:41:43,769 --> 00:41:46,772
I worked out a plan.

438
00:41:46,772 --> 00:41:50,209
Her soul will return on the 49th day

439
00:41:50,209 --> 00:41:52,700
before leaving for the next world.

440
00:41:52,945 --> 00:41:55,880
I wouldn't be scared this time.

441
00:42:06,692 --> 00:42:10,526
Granny, I'll challenge you.

442
00:42:18,537 --> 00:42:20,437
Come on!

443
00:42:53,672 --> 00:42:55,162
Why?

444
00:43:11,724 --> 00:43:15,285
Granny didn't come after all.

445
00:43:17,096 --> 00:43:20,122
Her soul must have come to rest.

446
00:43:39,051 --> 00:43:42,154
Granddad!

447
00:43:42,154 --> 00:43:45,824
The neighbors!

448
00:43:45,824 --> 00:43:49,453
Did you get scared?

449
00:44:01,106 --> 00:44:03,267
She'd got me.

450
00:44:06,178 --> 00:44:09,248
Come the anniversary of her death...

451
00:44:09,248 --> 00:44:11,682
I swear I wouldn't be scared.

452
00:44:13,519 --> 00:44:16,511
The End

